  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Our study provides a theory-grounded addition to the existing literature on social biases in language technologies.",
    "This body of work originated with studies into the social biases present in word embedding models trained on large language corpora 20, 64, 65.",
    "With the advent of modern deep-learning models, such investigations have extended to more complex architectures 66, 67.",
    "Although insightful, these studies have faced criticism for their lack of measurement validity, as well as insufficient conceptual grounding 30, 34.",
    "Furthermore, such studies typically treat bias against specific groups (for example, sexism or racism) in isolation [3] [4] [5], and forego the study of intergroup biases as posited by social psychology."
  ],
